<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5960] VirtualRandomAccessFile.close() is not idempotent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5960</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If VirtualRandomAccessFile.close() is called more than once, which might happen in code that cleans up after errors, it will throw a NullPointerException. We should make close() idempotent so that it is more robust.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
